**[1848] Ms.A.1.2.18.16**

Nathaniel Barney to RDW; Nantucket. He sorely regrets that he did not
see Pease while in England. “A South Car[olin]a slave-holder was our
fellow passenger from Liverpool, who told us he had crossed the Atlantic
to see Westminster Abbey, & Lord Wellington! I thought how different
were his aspirations from mine. True, I visited Westminster Abbey with
mingled emotions of pleasure & pain, but as regarded Lord Wellington, I
felt not the least ambition to look upon him.”


